<s docid="AP890107-0016" num="8" wdcount="37"> TOKYO (AP _ Emperor Hirohito 
will be remembered for one overwhelming decision during his 62-year 
reign: Japan must bow to defeat for the first time in its history and 
end the Pacific conflict in World War II.</s>

<s docid="AP890107-0119" num="9" wdcount="32"> World leaders sent Japan 
messages of condolences and some declared states of mourning after 
Emperor Hirohito's death Saturday, but painful memories of World War II 
still generated criticism of the Japanese monarch.</s>

<s docid="AP890107-0119" num="10" wdcount="25"> President Reagan said 
Hirohito's 62-year reign ``spanned one of the most tumultuous, and yet 
